<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta name="csrf-token" content={get_csrf_token()} />
    <title>Phoenix Static Strapi Example</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="header">
      <h1>Phoenix Static + Strapi CMS Example</h1>
      <nav class="nav">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <a href="/blog">Blog</a>
      </nav>
    </div>
    
    <main class="content">
      <section class="intro">
        <h2>Welcome!</h2>
        <p>This is a demonstration of how to use <strong>phoenix_static</strong> with Strapi CMS as a content source.</p>
        <p>This example shows how to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Fetch content from a Strapi REST API</li>
          <li>Generate static pages for blog posts and categories</li>
          <li>Handle relationships between content types</li>
          <li>Implement proper error handling and fallbacks</li>
        </ul>
        <p><a href="/blog">Visit the blog â†’</a></p>
      </section>
      
      <section class="setup">
        <h2>Setup Instructions</h2>
        <p>To run this example:</p>
        <ol>
          <li>Set up a Strapi CMS instance with Posts and Categories collections</li>
          <li>Configure the <code>STRAPI_URL</code> environment variable</li>
          <li>Run <code>mix deps.get</code> to install dependencies</li>
          <li>Start the Phoenix server with <code>mix phx.server</code></li>
        </ol>
        <p>See the README for detailed setup instructions.</p>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>